===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Oracle bone inscriptions: {{Han compound|鬲|又|ls=ic|t1=pot|t2=hand}} – a hand removing utensils after eating. Bronze inscriptions replaced {{zh-l|*又}} with {{zh-l|*攵}} to emphasize action.

In seal script {{zh-l|*彳}} was added to further emphasize action,  and what was originally a pot had corrupted into the unrelated {{zh-l|*育}}.

===Etymology===
The r-causative of {{och-l|逝}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Cognate with {{och-l|撤|to take away}}, {{och-l|滯|to discard; to leave over; to accumulate}} and perhaps {{och-l|適|id=1|to go}}.

